@realmoney Apr 01, 2020 | 07:50 AM EDT DOUG KASS Less Pontification, More Bottom-Up Ideas * Will be forthcoming... At all times, but particularly during a crisis, circulating bottom-up investment ideas is of paramount importance. Don't get me wrong, a market view is very

important - and so is the analytical discussion surrounding that market model. I have a view (sometimes strongly-held), as expressed daily in my Diary. That view is that, on an intermediate-term basis, numerous stocks provide exceptional upside reward vs. downside risk.

That said, though correlation has temporarily moved to one, stock picking will likely resume its importance in the next 12 months. So, as I previously have mentioned, while I plan to continue providing my thoughts about the stock market I will be providing a lot more bottom-up

company analysis as a menu for subscribers to consider. As an example, and over the last three days, I have updated my analysis of three banks (Bank of America ($BAC) , Citigroup ($C) and JP Morgan ($JPM) ) and I have mentioned

several new investment longs (including Hyatt ($H) , Hilton ($HLT) and Vornado ($VNO) , Verizon ($VZ) among others). You will see a lot more of this sort of company specific chatter and analysis going forward in my Diary. In my investing career, the sort of crisis that the world

faces today has provided a bonafide jumping point of opportunity to buy solid company franchises at a discount to intrinsic value. I see the Covid-19 inspired market and economic downturn as another one of those historically unique opportunities to realize potentially outsized

I promised myself that, going forward, I would restrict my comments about @realdonaldtrump on Twitter - as I believe it is now best that I commit my human and financial capital to defeating him in November. So I wanted to mention one and only one thing this morning.

At yesterday's multi hour press conference Trump continues to repeat the lie that “I shut down travel to China; otherwise things would have been much worse.” He did not “shut down” travel to China. On January 31, 2020, he prohibited non-US citizens from entering the US, who

had been in China in the prior fourteen days. Residents of the US continued to travel freely between the US and China. The virus could be—and was—carried into the US by a resident of Washington State. Read the official Proclamation for yourself. It also includes eleven exceptio

ns for non-US residents who were allowed to continue to travel between the US and China after January 31st. Trump did not “shut down the border with China.” Every time he says so, the press should report that “Trump repeated the lie that he shut down the border with China.”
